                                    <a class="SpecColor">2.</a> Think before posting<br>
                                    <a class="SpecColor">3.</a> Use trustworthy websites<br>
                                    <a class="SpecColor">4.</a> Use cryptic passcodes or passwords. Additionally suggested is the use of different passwords for every account.<br>
                                    <a class="SpecColor">5.</a> The controller of personal information is required to put reasonable and suitable safeguards in place to guard against unavoidable risks such unintentional loss or destruction.<br>
                                    <a class="SpecColor">6.</a> Watch out for phishing traps that are sent via email and for indicators of a cyber scam.<br>
                                    <a class="SpecColor">7.</a> Use unique backdrops, to prevent the unintentional revealing of personal information.</th>
                                <th class="tabHead2"><a class="SpecColor">1.</a> Sharing submissions for an unlimited time. (When the content no longer needs to be shared, delete it.)<br>
                                    <a class="SpecColor">2.</a> Spamming the chat.<br>
                                    <a class="SpecColor">3.</a> Sharing specific information<br>
                                    <a class="SpecColor">4.</a> Sharing account passwords<br>
                                    <a class="SpecColor">5.</a> Avoid clicking on links from unknown or untrustworthy sources.<br>
                                    <a class="SpecColor">6.</a> Do not open any suspicious emails or attachments.<br>
                                    <a class="SpecColor">7.</a> Never share your location to your viewers.</th>
